  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pacific Island Food Revolution</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Pacific Island Food Revolution (PIFR) is an innovative social and behaviour change communications programme that promotes healthy food in Fiji, PNG, Samoa, Tonga and Vanuatu.&#xA0;PIFR works to address the non-communicable disease (NCD) crisis in the Pacific, by encouraging Pacific people to prepare and eat healthy, traditional Pacific cuisine.&#xA0;It also works to increase demand for local produce. Through its focus on demand, the PIFR complements more production-focused support for agriculture.</narrative>
  </description>
